**ABOUT DESCARTES UNDERWRITING**


Descartes was born out of the conviction that the ever\\-increasing complexity of risks faced by corporations, governments and vulnerable communities calls for a renewed approach in insurance. Our team brings together industry veterans from the most renowned institutions (AXA, SCOR, Swiss Re, Marsh, Aon, ...) and scientists on top of their field to bring underwriting excellence. After 6 years of existence, Descartes has secured a leading position in parametric insurance for weather and climate\\-related risks utilizing machine learning, real\\-time monitoring from satellite imagery \\& IoT. After a successful Series B raise of $120M USD, we launched Descartes Insurance, a 'full stack' insurer licensed to underwrite risk by the French regulator ACPR. With a growing corporate client base (400\\+ and counting), our diverse team is headquartered in Paris and operates out of our 18 global offices in North America, Europe, Australia, Singapore, Hong Kong and Japan. Descartes is trusted by a panel of A\\-rated (re)insurers to carry out its activities.

**ABOUT YOUR ROLE**  

As part of the Product \\& Program team, we're looking for an individual to take on the role of Technical Product Owner. This position entails overseeing the development and evolution of technical projects/products tailored for advanced users, including underwriters, data scientists and software developers.  



**KEY MISSIONS**  



Project ownership



* You speak the same language as our Software, Data, and Devops Engineers: to understand the different components of a software system, you exchange very regularly with them to gather insight, understand needs and coordinate amongst the different engineering teams;
* You understand and know our technical end\\-users: beyond being completely fluent in software terminology and concepts, you also understand how the end\\-users interact with the software system and what they need to accomplish their missions;
* You co\\-define the project roadmap \\& manage a project backlog;
* You guarantee smooth communication amongst the different engineering teams and technical end\\-users, gathering feedback, tracking bug resolution and sharing a transparent backlog;
* You carry the product vision within Descartes: you have to communicate internally about your products, their evolutions and the vision they carry.



Project management



* You oversee the delivery process, ensuring that technical milestones are met and that deliverables align with project timelines and quality standards;
* You support cross\\-functional collaboration between software engineers to address any technical dependencies, unblock issues promptly, and maintain project flow;
* With your technical background, you work closely with software engineers to track and validate the quality of deliverables.

 **ABOUT YOU**  



EXPERIENCE \\& QUALIFICATIONS



* Completed a bachelor’s or master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or Information Technology;
* 3 years’ experience as a developer working with cross\\-functional teams including 1 year at Descartes.


SKILLS



* Technical Expertise: Prior software development experience in industry;
* Experience with APIs and cloud development (eg, GCP, AWS, Azure);
* Technical Project \\& Product Management Skills: Ability to manage, with a vision on business value, complex technical projects with contributors from multiple teams.
* Knowledge and prior experience in Agile methodologies (Scrum/Kanban). Creation and tracking of project/user KPIs;
* Communication: Good interpersonal skills \\& ability to work with technical profiles;
* Presentation: Ability to convey complex technical information in a clear and compelling manner;
* Fluent in French and English.



MINDSET

* Eager to learn more about the insurance industry;
* Results oriented, high energy, with the ability to work in a dynamic and multi\\-cultural environment;
* Excellent team player with an entrepreneurial mindset and value of diversity;
* Strong desire to learn and commitment to the organization’s mission.



*At Descartes Underwriting, we cherish value of diversity whatever it may be. We are committed to fighting against all forms of discrimination and for equal opportunities. We foster an inclusive work environment that respects all differences.*  

*With equal skills, all our positions are open to people with disabilities.*  



RECRUITMENT PROCESS FOR AN INTERNAL MOBILITY AT DESCARTES  

Pre\\-requisites to apply for any job in internal mobility :  

1\\. Have a performance that meets expectations so far;  

2\\. Minimum 1 year in your current position at Descartes at the time of internal mobility.  



Internal recruitment process :



* Step 1: HR Interview (Sana) to qualify if you’re eligible to apply based on your skills and motivations
* Step 2: If you are eligible, you should then inform your manager (who does have to “validate”)
* Step 3: Product Owner Case Study
* Step 4: Manager Interview with Camille Morel

**Descriptif du poste** 







 L’équipe Tech de Sidecare s’agrandit !




 En direct avec Louis, Cofondateur et CTO, et accompagné(e) par l’équipe Produit, tu participeras à toutes les étapes du développement et de la création d’une feature (code, test, scalabilité, performance et suivi d’utilisation) !










 Tu feras parti d’une équipe de 10 développeurs dont plusieurs Senior afin de te faire progresser très rapidement.










**Tes missions principales seront les suivantes :** 



* Participer à l’élaboration de nouvelles features en collaboration avec l’équipe Produit afin d’optimiser la solution pour la rendre plus performante pour les équipes G\\&A, Operations et Sales ;
* Contribuer à l’architecture de la plateforme, assurer la bonne qualité du code (création de tests \\& revues de code) et respecter les bonnes pratiques ;
* Analyser et corriger les anomalies dans nos différents environnements ;
* Être force de proposition et participer à l’évolution de la plateforme, nous recherchons des personnes qui veulent grandir et faire grandir SideCare !


- 


**Les avantages :** 




 Rejoindre SideCare c’est aussi :



* Des bureaux en plein cœur de Paris ;
* Carte titres\\-restaurants Swile ;
* Transport pris en charge à 50% ;
* Une ambiance de travail créative, sympa et focused ;
* Une carte Vélib’ gratuite
* Tous les premiers jeudis du mois, la boîte paie sa tournée !



 Et bien sûr tu seras hyper bien assuré(e)




 Télétravail : 2jours/semaine





**Profil recherché** 







 Ayant une formation en Ruby, tu es une personne curieuse, qui accorde de l’importance à la finalité produit et à l’expérience utilisateur !



* Tu as au moins un 2 ans d’expérience en développement fullstack sur Ruby on Rails
* Tu as un niveau de français (C2\\) et tu es basé(e) en IDF ;
* Tu t’intéresses aux rituels agiles et tu as envie de continuer à évoluer dans ce type d’environnement ;
* Tu sais communiquer facilement avec les autres équipes ;
* Tu as envie de continuer à apprendre et de monter rapidement en responsabilités (chez SideCare nous donnons très vite de l’ownership sur le développement de feature entière).








**Déroulement des entretiens** 






* Premier échange avec Lisa, Junior People Operation
* Cas pratique à effectuer en présentiel et debrief avec Chedli, Team Leader Dev
* Dernier échange avec Louis, CTO et co\\-fondateur de SideCare

